U.S. Silica Holdings, Inc. Key Developments

U.S. Silica Declares Quarterly Dividend, Payable on Oct. 3, 2017
Jul 24 17
U.S. Silica Holdings, Inc. announced that its Board of Directors has declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.0625 per common share. The dividend is payable on Oct. 3, 2017 for all shareholders of record as of the close of business on Sept. 15, 2017.


U.S. Silica Holdings Plans to Build New Frac Sand Mine and Plant in the Permian
Jun 12 17
U.S. Silica Holdings (SLCA) said that it will build a new frac sand mine and plant in West Texas to serve the Permian Basin. The facility is expected to produce 4 million tons annually and is part of the US Silica's previously announced plan to add 8 million tons to 10 million tons of new Brownfield and Greenfield capacity to meet demand. The $225 million project will be funded from cash on hand and cash flow from operations and is expected to be supported by long-term supply contracts with leading oilfield companies, which include cash pre-payments. Construction will begin immediately and initial production is scheduled for late in fourth quarter.


U.S. Silica Holdings, Inc. Presents at Citi 2017 Global Energy & Infrastructure Conference, May-11-2017
May 8 17
U.S. Silica Holdings, Inc. Presents at Citi 2017 Global Energy & Infrastructure Conference, May-11-2017 . Venue: The Four Seasons Hotel, Boston, Massachusetts, United States.


