You are hereHome » Locations » Berkeley Springs, WV 
Berkeley Springs, WV




 

Location 

OverviewProductsProduct DeliveryStakeholder Updates

Overview

Overview
U.S. Silica's Berkeley Springs plant has been mining the Oriskany deposit along the Warm Springs Ridge for over 100 years. The sand here is a 99.9% pure, buff-white sandstone that is low in iron, making it perfect for flat glass, specialty glass, building products, ceramics, paint, fillers, extenders, pool filtration and recreational use.
History
Mining at this location has been a part of the local landscape for over a century. The Pennsylvania Glass Sand Company, from Lewistown, PA, came into the area in the late 1800s and acquired much of the land − originally mined by many small family owned companies − and began what was then known as Berkeley Works. U.S. Silica, as it is known today, has undergone many developments over the years and has been a thriving part of the community, employing multiple generations of families from Berkeley Springs and the surrounding area.
Community
Many of the Berkeley Springs employees strive to be good neighbors and dedicate their free time to local fire and rescue organizations, youth leadership positions such as coaching and scouts, and to community needs like food drives. The plant also participates in an annual "adoption" of a needy family at Christmas and donates sand products for local recreational use. Recently the Berkeley Springs facility was honored with the 2009 Mountaineer Guardian Award for the effectiveness of the company's safety program.
Customer Service Contact
For questions concerning the status of your order, please contact your Customer Service Contact at:
Industrial Specialty ProductsISPCustomerCare@ussilica.com844-468-7263
Address
P.O. Box 187UPS – 2496 Hancock RoadBerkeley Springs, WV 25411Phone: (304) 258-2500
Driving Directions
From Maryland - Interstate 70
Follow I-70 West to Exit 1B (Route 522 South - Winchester, VA/Hancock, MD).  Exit will take you across the Potomac River to West Virginia.  Follow Route 522 for approximately 4.5 miles. The plant entrance is on the left.
From Maryland - Interstate 68
Follow I-68 East to Exit 82A (Route 522 South - Winchester, VA/Berkeley Springs). Exit will take you across the Potomac River to West Virginia.  Follow Route 522 for approximately 4.5 miles. The plant entrance is on left.
From Pennsylvania Turnpike 
Take Breezewood Exit off the Pennsylvania Turnpike.  Follow I-70 East to Exit 1B (Route 522 South - Winchester, VA/Hancock, MD).  Exit will take you across the Potomac River to West Virginia. Follow Route 522 for approximately 4.5 miles. The plant entrance is on the left.
From Virginia 
Follow Route 522 North from Winchester, VA (approximately 40 miles). Plant is 1 mile North of the Town of Berkeley Springs on the right.
From Martinsburg, WV
Follow Route 9 West to Berkeley Springs. Turn right on Route 522 North. Proceed approximately 2 miles. The plant entrance is on the right.
Berkeley Springs Downtown Warehouse
From the Berkeley Springs Plant, turn left on Route 522 South.  Follow for approximately 1 mile to the first traffic light (Union Street). Turn left on Union Street, street is one block long with the warehouse at the end.

 



